1
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,708
This was the interrogation room

2
00:00:25,703 --> 00:00:26,849
Interviewer: What do
you remember now?

3
00:00:30,703 --> 00:00:31,901
What do you remember now?

4
00:00:31,926 --> 00:00:35,000
I remember their
interrogators being here

5
00:00:36,797 --> 00:00:37,786
Interviewer: How
many interrogators?

6
00:00:37,865 --> 00:00:39,141
There were three interrogators

7
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:44,942
Three interrogators
were sitting here

8
00:00:47,676 --> 00:00:49,786
In this room, three were sitting

9
00:00:51,635 --> 00:00:52,624
Interviewer: How
were they sitting?

10
00:00:52,649 --> 00:00:54,812
They were sitting
at their tables here

11
00:00:55,593 --> 00:00:57,364
One of them would
interrogate you

12
00:00:58,041 --> 00:01:00,906
But they are three. Each
one has his own case

13
00:01:03,510 --> 00:01:06,140
Because they are
cases, not a single case

14
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:12,155
And each interrogator specializes
in different cases, like personal IDs

15
00:01:12,312 --> 00:01:14,968
And there are cases
for other charges

16
00:01:15,645 --> 00:01:19,630
Harassment cases too. They
have these matters as well

17
00:01:20,385 --> 00:01:22,702
Three interrogators
were sitting here

18
00:01:22,963 --> 00:01:25,671
They sit at the tables,
at three tables I saw

19
00:01:26,053 --> 00:01:27,329
Three sitting

20
00:01:30,636 --> 00:01:32,667
Interviewer: Who
was sitting here?

21
00:01:32,692 --> 00:01:35,974
When I entered here,
an interrogator was sitting

22
00:01:35,999 --> 00:01:37,875
Their judge

23
00:01:38,344 --> 00:01:39,568
And he said, What do you have?

24
00:01:40,063 --> 00:01:42,875
I wanted to take my personal ID, which
was confiscated at al-Salam Hospital

25
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:45,401
He asked, Why was
it taken from you?

26
00:01:45,948 --> 00:01:47,641
I told him, I saw a woman alone

27
00:01:48,136 --> 00:01:50,323
He said, Why did you let her ride with you when she
had no <i>mahram</i> [male guardian] ?

28
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,943
So he took the IDs and said to
me, Why did you argue with him?

29
00:01:54,646 --> 00:01:58,136
I said, What else did I say but, Are we
supposed to sit at home and not drive the taxi!?

30
00:01:58,579 --> 00:02:01,209
And earning a living
was already hard

31
00:02:01,886 --> 00:02:03,657
He said, Then leave
the job and stay at home

32
00:02:04,542 --> 00:02:08,683
I said, And what about the ten people
in the house—who will support them?

33
00:02:09,248 --> 00:02:10,785
He said, That's your problem

34
00:02:11,540 --> 00:02:15,134
So he sentenced me to 100 lashes

35
00:02:16,149 --> 00:02:18,832
They took me up to
the cell upstairs at noon

36
00:02:18,857 --> 00:02:22,660
The next day they
called me at 10 a.m.

37
00:02:23,129 --> 00:02:24,743
And they flogged me 100 lashes

38
00:02:25,576 --> 00:02:30,082
After that I went to collect
my personal ID from the center

39
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:33,024
There was a center at
the beginning of the street

40
00:02:33,389 --> 00:02:35,238
I took my ID from there and left

41
00:02:36,019 --> 00:02:38,806
After being flogged
upstairs, they brought me here

42
00:02:39,457 --> 00:02:43,155
The judge himself saw
my back after the flogging

43
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:45,707
To make sure my back was red

44
00:02:45,732 --> 00:02:47,295
Then he said, Go
and receive your ID

45
00:02:48,155 --> 00:02:50,238
So I left here and
went to collect the ID

46
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:53,670
They gave me a receipt slip

47
00:02:54,217 --> 00:02:57,915
And he told the ISIS member,
Go with him and give him his ID

48
00:03:01,535 --> 00:03:03,774
Interviewer: Describe your
feeling when you entered this room

49
00:03:03,799 --> 00:03:06,405
When you entered, was
this door open or closed?

50
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:12,082
And when the interrogators were
in front of you, how did you feel?

51
00:03:12,629 --> 00:03:16,431
I felt like someone walking
into prison—how would I feel?!

52
00:03:16,873 --> 00:03:18,306
What would you feel, I mean?

53
00:03:19,295 --> 00:03:22,967
You know you’ll be
flogged and imprisoned

54
00:03:22,992 --> 00:03:28,019
Either you’re jailed, or
they flog you and let you go

55
00:03:29,191 --> 00:03:30,415
One of the two

56
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,904
And because I argued
with them and yelled

57
00:03:35,476 --> 00:03:37,378
They flogged me 100 lashes

58
00:03:39,539 --> 00:03:43,393
Interviewer: Who interrogated
you—what was his nationality, his accent?

59
00:03:43,418 --> 00:03:45,320
His age, his appearance?

60
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,419
And was he masked?

61
00:03:48,444 --> 00:03:52,924
No, he wasn’t wearing a mask

62
00:03:52,949 --> 00:03:54,409
His beard was long

63
00:03:55,555 --> 00:04:01,753
Half of them were
from Mosul

64
00:04:07,638 --> 00:04:14,461
Interviewer: You didn’t even know
the name of the person sitting there?

65
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,776
They don’t call themselves by name...

66
00:04:17,801 --> 00:04:18,375
Only by noms de guerre

67
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,110
Abu Hurayra, Abu Omar

68
00:04:21,422 --> 00:04:22,646
Those are the names

69
00:04:24,105 --> 00:04:27,438
They don’t call
each other by name

70
00:04:28,089 --> 00:04:31,657
Abu so-and-so—his real name is
different, but they call him Abu so-and-so.

71
00:04:32,178 --> 00:04:34,391
He doesn’t have a
name they call him by

72
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:36,553
For example, you’re
so-and-so, you’re so-and-so

73
00:04:36,709 --> 00:04:39,651
Like Ahmad or Muhammad—no.

74
00:04:40,381 --> 00:04:41,891
Everyone chooses a
nickname for himself

75
00:04:44,417 --> 00:04:47,021
They call him by his
nickname, not his name

76
00:04:47,594 --> 00:04:50,433
So no one knows he’s
so-and-so, son of so-and-so

77
00:04:50,589 --> 00:04:52,881
Because then his real
identity would be known

78
00:04:54,292 --> 00:04:59,553
Interviewer: Can you describe that
moment exactly when you stood here?

79
00:04:59,578 --> 00:05:02,026
This door was closed

80
00:05:02,938 --> 00:05:04,969
All these windows were there

81
00:05:05,308 --> 00:05:08,484
I walked in and there was a
table here, right in this spot

82
00:05:09,188 --> 00:05:15,047
It was their table—the
ID judge’s table

83
00:05:15,568 --> 00:05:17,026
He asked me

84
00:05:18,016 --> 00:05:20,776
They handed him the
slip, they already had it.

85
00:05:21,011 --> 00:05:26,506
They gave him the slip and said, This
is because he argued with the brothers

86
00:05:27,938 --> 00:05:29,240
So he said, Why are you arguing?

87
00:05:29,265 --> 00:05:31,480
I told him, I work as a
taxi driver, trusting in God

88
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:33,849
And I argued with them

89
00:05:33,874 --> 00:05:34,396
He said, Why?

90
00:05:34,421 --> 00:05:35,959
I told him, We’ll quit
working and sit at home

91
00:05:35,984 --> 00:05:37,938
He told me, Quit working
and stay at home—don’t work.

92
00:05:38,823 --> 00:05:39,787
Those were his exact words

93
00:05:40,151 --> 00:05:42,469
He said, Come on, take
him to the detention upstairs

94
00:05:43,901 --> 00:05:46,870
Interviewer: When they brought you
in here, were your eyes blindfolded?

95
00:05:47,313 --> 00:05:48,901
No, they weren’t blindfolded

96
00:05:49,136 --> 00:05:51,506
Because my case wasn’t criminal

97
00:05:51,531 --> 00:05:52,730
Or a major charge

98
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:56,375
Only those who
had a criminal case...

99
00:05:57,417 --> 00:06:01,219
A serious charge—are
shackled and blindfolded

100
00:06:01,662 --> 00:06:04,396
But they brought me
from the center to here

101
00:06:05,204 --> 00:06:07,573
My eyes were open, and I
was walking normally beside him

102
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:09,917
But when we arrived, they took
me upstairs to the detention area

103
00:06:11,115 --> 00:06:13,459
After the interrogator
took my statement

104
00:06:13,928 --> 00:06:15,334
he led me upstairs
to the detention area

105
00:06:16,141 --> 00:06:18,224
He said, Let him learn
some manners for a while

106
00:06:20,855 --> 00:06:26,870
Interviewer: Were you sitting on
a chair during the interrogation?

107
00:06:26,895 --> 00:06:28,224
No, I was standing

108
00:06:29,917 --> 00:06:32,625
I stood on my feet, he asked me
the questions, and then I went upstairs

109
00:06:33,641 --> 00:06:37,756
Interviewer: Was the interrogation
recorded in audio or video?

110
00:06:38,849 --> 00:06:41,037
I didn’t pay attention to that

111
00:06:43,407 --> 00:06:45,698
Interviewer: What
questions did he ask you?

112
00:06:46,636 --> 00:06:50,047
He saw the slip and said
to me, Why are you arguing?

113
00:06:51,948 --> 00:06:56,037
I told him I wasn’t arguing; I just said,
We’ll quit working and stay at home

114
00:07:00,386 --> 00:07:05,776
Interviewer: In the questions he asked you,
do you think he already knew about you...

115
00:07:05,801 --> 00:07:10,594
before you entered, or did he begin
asking and learn from you when you came in?

116
00:07:10,619 --> 00:07:12,730
When they brought us, they
didn’t take us in right away

117
00:07:13,459 --> 00:07:16,141
They don’t let you in immediately;
they make you wait outside

118
00:07:17,313 --> 00:07:20,073
You stand at the door,
and the guard goes in

119
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:27,469
He asks him about
the case, and they talk

120
00:07:27,964 --> 00:07:29,839
Then he tells him, Bring
him in, meaning let him enter

121
00:07:30,724 --> 00:07:32,313
So you go in and tell him

122
00:07:37,678 --> 00:07:40,099
Interviewer: Were you brought
for interrogation only once?

123
00:07:40,124 --> 00:07:43,839
Yes, and when they flogged me, they brought me
before the investigative judge afterward to confirm

124
00:07:44,298 --> 00:07:47,579
He saw my back and the redness

125
00:07:47,604 --> 00:07:48,830
He said, Take him out now

126
00:07:48,855 --> 00:07:50,314
so I could go and retrieve my ID

127
00:07:50,965 --> 00:07:53,361
Interviewer: Didn’t they threaten you with anything?
Witness: No, they didn’t threaten me

128
00:07:53,725 --> 00:07:57,580
They just flogged me one
hundred lashes and released me

129
00:07:59,012 --> 00:08:05,027
Interviewer: So they didn’t threaten that if you did
it again, they’d put you in prison for a longer period?

130
00:08:05,052 --> 00:08:11,824
They tell you that the second time,
the reckoning will be without limit
